The time elapsed between a client sending a request to a server and the client receiving a response. It includes an average latency and a P99 latency.
Search latency is indicated by the purple line.

Monitor operation latency to track system efficiency.
To understand your system latency level, please refer to the

In most instances, a search request receives a response within milliseconds. If the response time extends to seconds or longer, it could indicate a cluster overload issue. It's worth noting that prolonged latencies can also arise when an excessive number of operations are batched into a single request.

Monitor the efficiency of data insertion.
When entity insert rate decreases, please consider scaling the cluster or adjusting the request rate.
